CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1956, page 13, reads: "Jewish War Veterans... presented their annual community service award to P. L. Prattis, executive editor, Pittsburgh Courier. Presentation was made at the twentieth annual Good-Will Dinner of the JWV's on Tuesday night with Judge Benjamin Lencher, left, doing the honors. Mr. Prattis (right) reads: the words on the bronze plaque while William Unger, chairman of the dinner, looks on. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of William Unger and Judge Benjamin Lencher presenting P. L. Prattis with plaque inscribed "Brotherhood award for community services rendered, presented to P. L. Prattis, by Pittsburgh post #49, Jewish War Veterans of the U.S.A., Tuesday, February 21st, 1956", standing in interior with brick walls and tapestry for the Jewish War Veterans Good-Will Dinner, horizontal format
